node.text:
Louvre has been one of the most visited museums in the world for several years. However, you can see not only the valuable historical and artistic exhibits. One of the main features of the world-famous museum is the ultramodern hydraulic elevator, which lifts visitors from the ground floor of the museum to the first floor.
#worldofengineering #mechanicalengineering #elevator #lift #louvre #france
Thanks to @yamada1998 for sharing

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by World of Engineering in London, United Kingdom with @forgottenheritage. May be an image of nature.

node.text:
With Luftwaffe bombers wanting as clear a path to London as possible, avoiding flying over land where flak batteries could target them. The Thames Estuary was seen as the safest route right into the heart of the city. Recognising this weakness the British army enlisted the help of civil engineer, Guy Maunsell. His solution was to build metal and concrete gun towers that could be built on land and then towed out to sea and sunk onto the seabed. They were grouped together as clusters of seven towers covered in heavy machine guns and Bofor canons and formed a very effective deterrent, it wasn't long before the bombers were rerouted. This was taken from the roof of one of the towers during a rare working party trip by @forgottenheritage 

#worldofengineering #engineering #history #civilengineering #civilengineer #engineer

node.text:
How do erasable pens work?

The ink has three components. One component is a pigment (the color) that reacts to acidity by turning invisible. The second component is a chemical that acts as an acid or a base. The third component reacts to heat by activating the acid/base.
When you erase with the rubber, the friction creates heat which changes the acidity of the ink and makes it invisible.

#worldofengineering #science #tech #chemistry #physics #pen #officesupplies

node.text:
DIY WiFi door lock with NodeMCU. NodeMCU is an open source IoT platform. It includes firmware which runs on the ESP8266 Wi-Fi SoC from Espressif Systems, and hardware which is based on the ESP-12 module. The term ""NodeMCU"" by default refers to the firmware rather than the development kits. The firmware uses the Lua scripting language.

Courtesy of @orad.e

#worldofengineering #engineering #computing #programming #nodemcu #automation #electronics
